European Stocks, U.S. Futures Rise; Akzo Nobel, William Hill Shares Climb

-- B y   J u l i e   C r u z
-- 
2011-04-21T08:05:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/european-stocks-u-s-futures-rise-akzo-nobel-william-hill-shares-climb.html
European stocks rose, with the
benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index gaining 0.3 percent to 279.95
as of 9:03 a.m. London time. The measure is headed for a weekly
advance.  Akzo Nobel soared 4.1 percent after the world’s biggest
maker of paints reported increased first-quarter profit. William
Hill Plc surged 7.7 percent as the bookmaker’s sales rose.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Julie Cruz at 
 jcruz6@bloomberg.net  